{
  "stem": "3874.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "There was constant-- the correspondence constantly said, we're coming soon, we're coming soon.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And I recall one letter, which I still have a copy of, but it said, well, it looks like we're only waiting for one more papers, because it looks like we're getting a visa to the United States and we're going to settle in Los Angeles.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And it was going to happen very imminently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Well, obviously, it never occurred.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "September, 1939 is when World War II broke out, when the Germans invaded Poland.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Things started changing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Until then, by the way, the life in Eaubonne, this home, the children's home, was very, very pleasant.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "There was food.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "It was-- you know, we went to-- we went to school, we had friends, we played football, we were corresponding with parents.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the only negative that I could see is that I missed my parents, especially on visitor day when other people received visitors and I didn't.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "After September, 1939, when the war broke out, things changed again.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I-- we could no longer correspond with our parents, OK, except that I was very lucky.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We had, a-- either a relative or a friend in Switzerland.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "So my parents would write them, they would forward the letters to me, and I would then return letters to Switzerland to my parents.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So I was able to still correspond with them.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And so anybody who had a kind of a contact, I would take letters from some of the other children who wanted to correspond with their parents, and send it through Switzerland, so that other children were able to correspond with the parents.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And anybody who had any kind of a contact was doing this.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
